    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "That's certainly buggy!\n\nBut I think the categorical assignment is more comparable to assigning with numpy arrays (they also don't have an index), so it should follow this behaviour:\n\n```\nIn [86]: df['f'] = np.array([1])\n...\nValueError: Length of values does not match length of index\n\nIn [87]: df['f'] = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4])\n...\nValueError: Length of values does not match length of index\n\n```\n"
  },
